Four people have been killed in a car crash in Limpopo on SundayThe accident, which happened in Thohoyandou, occurred at about 5 am.&#8220;The police in Thohoyandou are investigating a case of culpable homicide,&#8221; said Police Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe.It is alleged that a white Toyota double cab lost control and avoided with the tree alongside the road instantly killing four passengers and the drive.Ngoepe said three other passengers sustained serious injuries and were taken to Elim Hospital for medical treatment.&#8220;The identities of all the deceased are still unknown at this stage,&#8221; he said.The cause of this accident is still unknown but police investigations are continuing.TNA Reporter 